“What a legendary actor. He was television’s finest. He ensured he nailed all his on-screen characters so much that you had no choice but to love him.” This was shared across social platforms as family, friends and fans are reeling after the news of the death of multi award-winning South African actor Jamie Bartlett. Bartlett, 55, was best known for his portrayal of David Genaro on soapie, ‘Rhythm City’. He also played the role of Mike O’Reilly in the soapie 'Isidingo’. Bartlett was born in Maidenhead, England to a South African mother and a British father. The renowned actor took on local and international roles and appeared in numerous stage plays, television productions and feature films. In 2019, he won an award at The South African Film and Television Awards for his role as David Genaro. Actor Spaces, a platform which celebrates excellence in the African Film, Television and Theatre industry, wrote on Instagram. “RIP veteran actor Jamie Bartlett. Screen and theatre actor Jamie Bartlett has sadly passed away. He appeared in numerous stage plays, television productions and feature films. Best known for his portrayal as David Genaro in Rhythm City and many more iconic roles. Our deepest condolences to his family, friends, colleagues and fans. Jamie’s work will live on.” There are no details yet of Bartlett’s memorial service and funeral.